Step One: go to https://www.phpmyadmin.net/
                                            
                    > Click on "Support" Tab on top of page
                          
                                        > Under the header "Read the documentation!" click on "the documentation"
                                        
                                                                     > Click on "Installing on Windows"
                                                                     
                                                                                     > Click on XAMPP
                                                                                     
                                                                                            > Install on C:
                                            


Step Two: After installing XAMPP go to:

                     > xampp

                         > htdocs
                         
                             > create the folder containin the HTML and PHP files we will be creating.
                             

Test the files on a Chrome Browser.

Step Three: Download XAMPP, which will contain phpMyAdmin.
            The Set up steps are found here: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=S8pL5qd1b30
            The Final Step: Choose Apache and MySQL to Start and Stop

Step Four: Open a browser, type in "localhost," which will direct you to the XAMPP Apache dashboard. Select phpMyAdmin.
